sndlib.ext.generators.gml
Class SolutionGmlProperties

java.lang.Object
  com.atesio.gml.gen.GmlProperties
      sndlib.ext.generators.gml.BaseGmlProperties
          sndlib.ext.generators.gml.SolutionGmlProperties

public class SolutionGmlProperties
extends BaseGmlProperties

This class collects the properties to be used when generating a GML for a SolvedProblem.

Note: The support of property values resp. their ranges depends on the used visualizer. We can recommend the free graph editor yEd, which is a simple, easy to use tool for viewing, editing and analyzing GML graphs.
Some style constants supported by yEd are collected in GmlStyles.

Author:
Roman Klaehne
See Also:
GmlStyles, SolutionGmlGenerator

See setLinkColorGradientType(GradientType) for more information about what the gradient type means.

If no individual gradient type was set, explicitely by setLinkColorGradientType(GradientType) or implicitely by load(Properties), the default type SolutionGmlProperties.Defaults.LINK_COLOR_GRADIENT_TYPE is returned.

Returns:
the link color gradient type
See Also:

setLinkColorGradientType

public void setLinkColorGradientType(SolutionGmlProperties.GradientType linkColorGradientType)
Sets the gradient type to be used when determining the color of links in the solution GML.
The link color gradient is defined by its start/end-color and its resolution. The lower the value of a link regarding the gradient type the closer is its color to the start-color.
Given, e.g., red/black as start/end-color and assuming the SolutionGmlProperties.GradientType.USAGE gradient type, then the color of links with low usage will be some kind of red while black links indicate full use of the capacity.

Parameters:
linkColorGradientType - the gradient type
See Also:
setLinkColorGradientResolution(int), setLinkColorGradientStart(Color), setLinkColorGradientEnd(Color)

setLinkColorGradientResolution

public void setLinkColorGradientResolution(int linkColorGradientResolution)
Sets the resolution of the link color gradient.
The resolution defines the length of the color sequence which constitutes the color gradient. This color sequence starts at the start-color and ends at the end-color, to be defined by setLinkColorGradientStart(Color) resp. setLinkColorGradientEnd(Color).

Given, e.g., a resolution of r, the links are distributed on r classes, according to the property of the gradient type. To each of these classes one of the r colors is assigned.
If r == 1, all links share the same color, namely the start-color.
If r < 1, it is treated as it would be 1.

Parameters:
linkColorGradientResolution - the resolution of the link color gradient
See Also:
setLinkColorGradientType(GradientType), setLinkColorGradientStart(Color), setLinkColorGradientEnd(Color)

setLinkWidthGradientType

public void setLinkWidthGradientType(SolutionGmlProperties.GradientType linkWidthGradientType)
Sets the gradient type to be used when determining the width of links in the solution GML.
The link width gradient is only defined by its resolution.
Assuming, e.g., a resolution of r and the SolutionGmlProperties.GradientType.CAPACITY gradient type then the link width vary from 1 to r, according to the capacity which is installed on the link. The more capacity is installed on the link the thicker will be its width in the solution GML. A width near 1 is assigned to links with low capacity while highest capacity links will get the thickest width r.

Parameters:
linkWidthGradientType - the link width gradient type
See Also:
setLinkWidthGradientResolution(int)

the resolution of the link width gradient

Sets the resolution of the link width gradient.
Given, e.g., a resolution of r, the links are distributed on r classes, according to the property of the gradient type. To each of these classes one of the widths varying from 1 to r is assigned.

Parameters:
